ok]]'' as ''When the Devil Drives.''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995544\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995544&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995544&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Period Stuff''\n| 1942\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n| Short stories, some originally published in ''[[The Windsor Magazine]]'' and others in ''[[The Strand Magazine]]''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995536\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995536&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995536&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Lower than Vermin''\n| 1950\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n| \n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995532\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995532&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995532&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Ne'er-Do-Well''\n| 1954\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n| Yates's only detective story.<ref name=\"SmithersAppx\" />\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995535\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995535&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995535&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Wife Apparent]]''\n| 1956\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n| Originally intended to be called ''Lady in Waiting'' but the title was changed after the dust-cover had been printed due to another book with that title being published. First editions had the title over-printed with an explanatory note from the author. \n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995550\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc