odder & Stoughton|Hodder and Stoughton]]''\n| \n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995541\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995541&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995541&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''An Eye for a Tooth''\n| 1943\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n| \n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995526\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995526&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995526&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Red in the Morning''\n| 1946\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n|''Were Death Denied'' in the US.<ref name=\"Macdonald\"/> follows on directly from ''Gale Warning''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995538\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995538&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995538&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Cost Price''\n|1949\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n|''The Laughing Bacchante'' in the US.<ref name=\"Macdonald\"/> Sequel to ''Safe Custody'' [see table below]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995524\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995524&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995524&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Other fiction ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|+\nOther fiction\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year of first<br />publication\n! scope=\"col\" | First edition publisher<br />\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |{{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Anthony Lyveden''\n| 1921\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n| Originally published in ''[[The Windsor Magazine]]''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995513\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995513&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995513&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Valerie French''\n| 1923\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n|Sequel to ''Anthony Lyveden''. Originally published in ''[[The Windsor Magazine]]''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995549\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995549&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995549&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''And Five Were Foolish''\n| 1924\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n|Short stories, originally published in ''[[The Windsor Magazine]]''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995512\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995512&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995512&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''As Other Men Are''\n| 1925\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n| Short stories, originally published in ''[[The Windsor Magazine]]''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995515\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995515&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995515&nbsp;|website=primocat.bl.uk|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''The Stolen March''\n| 1926\n|[[Ward Lock & Co]]\n| Fantasy novel, originally published in ''[[The Windsor Magazine]]''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"BLcat003995545\">{{Cite web|url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995545&con_lng=eng|title=British Library details for item 003995545&nbsp;|website=primoca